org.openbel.framework.api
Class DefaultKamCacheService

java.lang.Object
  org.openbel.framework.api.DefaultKamCacheService
All Implemented Interfaces:
KamCacheService
public class DefaultKamCacheService
extends Object
implements KamCacheService

Default thread-safe implementation of a KamCacheService.

Maps

This implementation maintains three separate maps internally.
KAM map
Maintains a strong reference to a Kam object by its handle (a string)
Unfiltered map
Maintains a reference to handles available by KAMCatalogDao.KamInfo. This allows calls to the interface to return a handle to the KAM held in memory when KamFilter is not provided
Filtered map
Maintains a reference to handles available by KAMCatalogDao.KamInfo and KAMCatalogDao.KamFilter. This allows calls to the interface to return a handle to the KAM held in memory when KamFilter is provided

Thread-safety

Access to any of the maps is done under a single read lock. Mutating any of the maps is done under a single write lock. Both locks are contended for in a fair fashion.

Concurrent Loading

The number of KAMs that can be loaded concurrently is controlled by the CONCURRENT_LOAD constant.

Author:
julianray
